mods.abstract: Nicholas Gerber was born in New York City in 1962. At age eight, he moved to Chappaqua, New York where he attended Horace Greeley High School. He earned his M.B.A from the University of San Francisco in 1989 and his B.A. of Economics from Skidmore College in 1984. While pursuing his degrees, Nicholas began to apply himself in the investment world. Nicholas interned at Bedell Investment Counseling as a Research Analyst during 1988. From 1986 to 1989 Nicholas was a General Trading Partner at Victory Fund I, where Nicholas was responsible for advising courses of actions for $450,000 in stock index futures. After finishing his education, Nicholas became a Financial Analyst/Appraiser at Value Research Corporation in Los Angeles.
